The paper deals with the study of relationships between interval and cocomparability graphs, which are both topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper proposes a new algorithm for finding maximal interval subgraphs and simplicial vertices in cocomparability graphs, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) and algorithms (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses lattice structures, which are relevant to the field of theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
